The U.S. bombed a Sudanese pharmaceutical factory in retaliation for the 1998 bombings of the U.S. Embassies in Kenya and Tanzania. 
 The U.S. said it was targeting a terrorist chemical plant linked to al-Qaida leader Osama bin Laden. 
 Sudan accused the U.S. of violating its sovereignty. 
 The Arab Group of states and Islamic states met at the U.N. to express support for Sudan's effort.